<p local-id=3D"69c079b18dc5">below 60%</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"fa4a111960c3">Grading criteria for certain assignments may b=
e formalized into "grading rubrics." These rubrics can help students better=
 understand how their work will be evaluated. &nbsp;</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"e9afdde77339" id=3D"Syllabus-AdditionalAdministrativePolici=
es">Additional Administrative Policies</h3>
<p local-id=3D"f3d2489de4af"><strong>Student Responsibility</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"1c98b88dc9d9">This course abides by all college and Universi=
ty policies. Students are responsible for knowing and adhering to policies =
in the College Handbook and University polices.</p>
<p local-id=3D"e42e236b7b14">Policy:<strong> </strong><a class=3D"external-=
link" href=3D"https://www.jefferson.edu/life-at-jefferson/handbooks.html" r=
el=3D"nofollow"><strong>College and University Policies &amp; Handbooks</st=
rong></a></p>
<p local-id=3D"8cbd1b0150ac"><strong>Add/Drop/Withdrawal:</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"950f20b37c71">Course add/drop dates are posted in the offici=
al University calendar. Refer to your program's calendar for related deadli=
nes (<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://www.jefferson.edu/registrar=
/academic-calendars.html" rel=3D"nofollow">JCPH Academic Calendars</a>). Re=
fer to the University Tuition Refund Policy (<a class=3D"external-link" hre=
f=3D"https://www.jefferson.edu/life-at-jefferson/handbooks/policies/undergr=
aduate-policies/tuition-and-university-fees-refund.html" rel=3D"nofollow">T=
JU Tuition Refund Policy</a>) for information regarding tuition reimburseme=
nt following dropped classes after the withdrawal period.</p>
<p local-id=3D"af24749e4dbe"><strong>Changes to Posted Syllabus:</strong></=
p>
<p local-id=3D"746451ee03f5">Provided adequate advance notice is given to t=
he class, the instructor reserves the right to modify the syllabus and clas=
s activities or requirements in order to enhance learning during the delive=
ry of the course. Such modifications can include but are not limited to sub=
stitutions of certain journal articles or other periodical resources for ot=
hers, changes to the details of particular assignments, rearrangement of gr=
oup activities, or modification of class participation requirements. Any su=
ch changes will be designed so as not to unduly impact student schedules or=
 the overall workload for the course.</p>
<p local-id=3D"54e0ed7f6e5f"><strong>Chosen Name</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"588e68a18e66">Some members of our community use a name, gend=
er, and pronoun other than their legal identifiers. Students are free to el=
ect to have their chosen first name, gender identity and chosen pronoun app=
ear in Thomas Jefferson University=E2=80=99s system.</p>
<p local-id=3D"848fc584f03f">Policy: <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"htt=
ps://www.jefferson.edu/life-at-jefferson/handbooks/policies/graduate-polici=
es.html" rel=3D"nofollow"><strong>Graduate Policy</strong></a><br>
Policy: <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://www.jefferson.edu/life-a=
t-jefferson/handbooks/policies/undergraduate-policies/chosen-name.html" rel=
=3D"nofollow"><strong>Undergraduate Policy</strong></a></p>
<p local-id=3D"595090b436c7"><strong>Collection of Student Work:</strong></=
p>
<p local-id=3D"4f670028dc0b">Thomas Jefferson University has the right to r=
etain representative examples or copies of student work from all courses. S=
uch materials might include papers, exams, creative works, or portfolios de=
veloped and submitted in courses or to satisfy the requirements for degree =
programs as well as surveys, focus group information, and reflective exerci=
ses.</p>
<p local-id=3D"508fa762fded"><strong>Diversity &amp; Inclusion:</strong></p=
>
<p local-id=3D"f62767ca5ce2">Jefferson holds itself accountable, at every l=
evel of the organization, to nurture an environment of inclusion and respec=
t, by valuing the uniqueness of every individual, celebrating and reflectin=
g the rich diversity of its communities, and taking meaningful action to cu=
ltivate an environment of fairness, belonging, and opportunity.</p>
<p local-id=3D"bdfab8b2f3f5">&nbsp;Policy:<a class=3D"external-link" href=
=3D"https://www.jefferson.edu/academics/colleges-schools-institutes/skmc/di=
versity.html" rel=3D"nofollow"></a><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https=
://belonging.jefferson.edu/" rel=3D"nofollow"><strong>Community Impact and =
Belonging</strong></a></p>
<p local-id=3D"5391752f518c"><strong>Copyright Notice:</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"f675a1bed512">All information presented in this course is co=
pyrighted.&nbsp; This includes, but is not limited to, lecture notes, recor=
ded lectures, handouts, journal articles, technical reports, videos, and we=
b pages.&nbsp; Students are prohibited from sharing any course information =
with anyone outside of this class.&nbsp; This includes posting information =
on Facebook, FlashNotes, or other online service; emailing information; or =
any other form of distribution.</p>
<p local-id=3D"f3ed29baefcc"><strong>Course Enrollment</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"3a38e3285789">Students must be officially enrolled in this c=
ourse to attend and are continuously enrolled until official drop/ withdraw=
 from the course.</p>
<p local-id=3D"fca9c987c999"><strong>Disability Accommodations:</strong></p=
>
<p local-id=3D"b4d72425a55d">Thomas Jefferson University is committed to pr=
oviding equal education opportunities to all students, including students w=
ith disabilities, in accordance with section 504 of the Rehabilitation Act =
of 1973 and the Americans with Disabilities Act. Thomas Jefferson Universit=
y will provide reasonable accommodations to all qualified individuals with =
disabilities to allow equal access and full participation to all University=
 sponsored activities and programs.</p>
<p local-id=3D"3bb7975b1c34">&nbsp;Policy: <a class=3D"external-link" href=
=3D"https://www.jefferson.edu/life-at-jefferson/handbooks/rights-responsibi=
lities/disability-accommodations.html" rel=3D"nofollow"><strong>Rights &amp=
; Responsibilities</strong></a></p>
<p local-id=3D"e35f05c6528f"><strong>Registration Status:</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"2a274065e126">Students are responsible for the status of the=
ir registration at all times.&nbsp; The instructor will advise that a chang=
e in status has occurred when so informed by the College/University.&nbsp; =
Only students who are properly registered in this course can earn credit an=
d receive a grade.</p>
<p local-id=3D"b8ee82d0786b"><strong>Student Religious Observation Policy</=
strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"9e530b42912a">Thomas Jefferson University understands that s=
ome students may seek to observe religious holidays that fall on scheduled =
class days.</p>
<p local-id=3D"81ca46aa0dbc">Policy: <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"htt=
ps://www.jefferson.edu/life-at-jefferson/handbooks/policies/graduate-polici=
es/student-religious-observance-policy.html" rel=3D"nofollow"><strong>Gradu=
ate Programs</strong></a><br>
Policy <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://www.jefferson.edu/life-at=
-jefferson/handbooks/policies/undergraduate-policies/student-religious-obse=
rvance-policy.html" rel=3D"nofollow"><strong>Undergraduate Programs</strong=
></a></p>
<p local-id=3D"3a9bc397a85b"><strong>Retention of Student Work</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"0e3485cb9eb1">Thomas Jefferson University has the right to r=
etain representative examples or copies of student work from all courses. S=
uch materials might include papers, exams, creative works, or portfolios de=
veloped and submitted in courses or to satisfy the requirements for degree =
programs as well as surveys, focus group information, and reflective exerci=
ses.</p>
<p local-id=3D"698776d37fa7"><strong>Title IX &amp; Sexual Misconduct</stro=
ng></p>
<p local-id=3D"18f21ef51045">The University=E2=80=99s Sex and Gender-Based =
Misconduct Policy sets forth Jefferson=E2=80=99s commitment to foster an en=
vironment free of discrimination, including sexual harassment and sexual vi=
olence.</p>
<p local-id=3D"89615354a073">Policy: <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"htt=
ps://www.jefferson.edu/life-at-jefferson/student-resources-services/academi=
